            "text": "A janitor making $4/hour walked into a Fortune 500 company boardroom. Shaking, he took a seat opposite the CEO.\n\n\"So I had an idea...\" he nervously began.\n\nYears later, that idea would become an iconic consumer brand and make him worth ~$20M.\n\nHere's how that meeting went üß∂üëá",
            "author_id": "996386814297505792"
        },
        {
            "lang": "en",
            "conversation_id": "1341193051184611331",
            "id": "1341193055425085442",
            "attachments": {
                "media_keys": [
                    "3_1341190544723099649"
                ]
            },
            "created_at": "2020-12-22T01:25:17.000Z",
            "author_id": "996386814297505792",
            "referenced_tweets": [
                {
                    "type": "replied_to",
                    "id": "1341193051184611331"
                }
            ],
            "text": "1) Richard Monta√±ez grew up in Cucamonga Valley, California, sharing a one-room cinderblock hut with 14 family members.\n\nHe dreaded school. Barely able to speak English, he‚Äôd cry to his mother as she was getting him ready for class. https://t.co/2DbDaGmBqh"
        },
        {
            "lang": "en",
            "conversation_id": "1341193051184611331",
            "id": "1341193056825999362",
            "created_at": "2020-12-22T01:25:17.000Z",
            "author_id": "996386814297505792",
            "referenced_tweets": [
                {
                    "type": "replied_to",
                    "id": "1341193055425085442"
                }
            ],
            "text": "2) When asked, all other students in class would eagerly shout out their dream job: Astronaut, Doctor, Racecar driver. \n\nRichard had nothing to say. ‚ÄúThere was no dream where I came from.‚Äù"
        },
        {
            "lang": "en",
            "conversation_id": "1341193051184611331",
            "id": "1341193057966772226",
            "created_at": "2020-12-22T01:25:17.000Z",
            "author_id": "996386814297505792",
            "referenced_tweets": [
                {
                    "type": "replied_to",
                    "id": "1341193056825999362"
                }
            ],
            "text": "3) He dropped out of school in 4th grade and took odd jobs at farms and factories to help make ends meet.\n\nSome years later in 1976, a neighbor let him know of a job opening for a factory janitor at the Frito-Lay plant down the road. The $4/hour pay was more than he'd ever made."
        },
        {
            "lang": "en",
            "conversation_id": "1341193051184611331",
            "id": "1341193062366601216",
            "attachments": {
                "media_keys": [
                    "3_1341190674599747586"
                ]
            },
            "created_at": "2020-12-22T01:25:18.000Z",
            "author_id": "996386814297505792",
            "referenced_tweets": [
                {
                    "type": "replied_to",
                    "id": "1341193057966772226"
                }
            ],
            "text": "4) As he was getting ready for his first day of work, his grandfather pulled him aside and said:\n\n‚ÄúMake sure that floor shines. And let them know that a Monta√±ez mopped it.‚Äù https://t.co/qnKN84na2W"
        },
        {
            "lang": "en",
            "conversation_id": "1341193051184611331",
            "id": "1341193064451166208",
            "created_at": "2020-12-22T01:25:19.000Z",
            "author_id": "996386814297505792",
            "referenced_tweets": [
                {
                    "type": "replied_to",
                    "id": "1341193062366601216"
                }
            ],
            "text": "5) Richard made it his mission to be the best janitor Frito-Lay had ever seen. \n\nHe spent his off-time learning about the company's products, manufacturing, marketing and more. He even asked salesmen to tag along and watch them sell."
        },
        {
            "lang": "en",
            "conversation_id": "1341193051184611331",
            "id": "1341193066003062786",
            "created_at": "2020-12-22T01:25:19.000Z",
            "author_id": "996386814297505792",
            "referenced_tweets": [
                {
                    "type": "replied_to",
                    "id": "1341193064451166208"
                }
            ],
            "text": "6) In the mid-1980s Frito-Lay started to struggle. The CEO announced a new initiative to all 300,000 employees. ‚ÄúAct like an owner‚Äù Trying to empower them to work more creatively and efficiently.\n\nMonta√±ez listened."
        },
        {
            "lang": "en",
            "conversation_id": "1341193051184611331",
            "id": "1341193067450142720",
            "created_at": "2020-12-22T01:25:20.000Z",
            "author_id": "996386814297505792",
            "referenced_tweets": [
                {
                    "type": "replied_to",
                    "id": "1341193066003062786"
                }
            ],
            "text": "7) Then, he called the CEO.\n\n‚ÄúMr. Enrico‚Äôs office. Who is this?‚Äù\n‚ÄúRichard Monta√±ez, in California‚Äù\n‚ÄúYou‚Äôre the VP overseeing CA?‚Äù\n‚ÄúNo, I work at the Rancho Cucamonga plant.‚Äù\n‚ÄúOh, so you‚Äôre the VP of Ops?‚Äù\n‚ÄúNo, I work inside the plant.‚Äù\n‚ÄúYou‚Äôre the manager?‚Äù\n‚ÄúNo. I‚Äôm the janitor.‚Äù"
        },
        {
            "lang": "en",
            "conversation_id": "1341193051184611331",
            "id": "1341193068901351424",
            "created_at": "2020-12-22T01:25:20.000Z",
            "author_id": "996386814297505792",
            "referenced_tweets": [
                {
                    "type": "replied_to",
                    "id": "1341193067450142720"
                }
            ],
            "text": "8) The CEO got on the line. Loving the initiative, he told Richard to prepare a presentation, and he set a meeting in 2 weeks time.\n\nStunned, Richard ran to the library and picked up a book on marketing strategies. Then, he started prepping."
        },
        {
            "lang": "en",
            "conversation_id": "1341193051184611331",
            "id": "1341193072089079809",
            "attachments": {
                "media_keys": [
                    "3_1341192193931821056"
                ]
            },
            "created_at": "2020-12-22T01:25:21.000Z",
            "author_id": "996386814297505792",
            "referenced_tweets": [
                {
                    "type": "replied_to",
                    "id": "1341193068901351424"
                }
            ],
            "text": "9) 2 weeks later, he entered that boardroom. \n\nAfter taking a moment to catch his breath, he started telling them what he'd learned about Frito-Lay and the idea he'd been working on. https://t.co/u4l4lhDWmy"
        },
        {
            "lang": "en",
            "conversation_id": "1341193051184611331",
            "id": "1341193073355735040",
            "created_at": "2020-12-22T01:25:21.000Z",
            "author_id": "996386814297505792",
            "referenced_tweets": [
                {
                    "type": "replied_to",
                    "id": "1341193072089079809"
                }
            ],
            "text": "10) ‚ÄúI saw there was no product catering to Latinos.‚Äù\n\nOn the sales trips he shadowed he saw that in Latino neighborhoods Lays, Fritos, Ruffles, and Cheetos, were stocked right next to a shelf of Mexican spices. Frito-Lay had nothing spicy or hot."
        },
        {
            "lang": "en",
            "conversation_id": "1341193051184611331",
            "id": "1341193076388163586",
            "attachments": {
                "media_keys": [
                    "3_1341191059863293952"
                ]
            },
            "created_at": "2020-12-22T01:25:22.000Z",
            "author_id": "996386814297505792",
            "referenced_tweets": [
                {
                    "type": "replied_to",
                    "id": "1341193073355735040"
                }
            ],
            "text": "11) The Latino market was ready to explode, Monte√±ez explained.\n\nInspired by elote - a Mexican street corn covered in spices - Richard had created his own snack\n\nHe pulled out 100 plastic baggies. He had taken Cheetos from the factory and coated them in his own mix of spices https://t.co/7yLtX1PFfp"
        },
        {
            "lang": "en",
            "conversation_id": "1341193051184611331",
            "id": "1341193077701005313",
            "created_at": "2020-12-22T01:25:22.000Z",
            "author_id": "996386814297505792",
            "referenced_tweets": [
                {
                    "type": "replied_to",
                    "id": "1341193076388163586"
                }
            ],
            "text": "12) He‚Äôd even sealed the bags with a clothing iron, and had hand drawn a logo on each one. \n\nThe room went silent.\n\nAfter a few moments, the CEO spoke, ‚ÄúPut that mop away, you‚Äôre coming with us‚Äù"
        },
        {
            "lang": "en",
            "conversation_id": "1341193051184611331",
            "id": "1341193081522012160",
            "attachments": {
                "media_keys": [
                    "3_1341191370459938816"
                ]
            },
            "created_at": "2020-12-22T01:25:23.000Z",
            "author_id": "996386814297505792",
            "referenced_tweets": [
                {
                    "type": "replied_to",
                    "id": "1341193077701005313"
                }
            ],
            "text": "13) Flamin‚Äô Hot Cheetos became one of the most successful launches in Frito-Lay history. They went on to become a viral, pop-culture sensation. \n\nRichard became a VP and amassed a $20M fortune.\n\nNot bad for a boy from Cucamonga. https://t.co/DLUhCWQ9C5"
        },
        {
            "lang": "en",
            "conversation_id": "1341193051184611331",
            "id": "1341472204035276800",
            "created_at": "2020-12-22T19:54:31.000Z",
            "author_id": "996386814297505792",
            "referenced_tweets": [
                {
                    "type": "replied_to",
